        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 29 at 7:53PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 752 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 13 miles west of Lake Pleasant to near
Dolgeville to Richfield Springs. Movement was east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Meco, Charleston, Whitehouse, Mindenville, Ripple Corners, Garnet
Lake, Powley Place, Hope Falls, Lake Pleasant, Yosts, Dwelly Corners,
Northampton Beach Public Campground, Schuyler Corners, Knowelhurst,
Emmonsburg, Red Bunch Corners, Edicks, Christmans Corners, Hill
Corners, and Gloversville.

This includes Interstate 90 between exits 27 and 29A.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for
eastern and east central New York.</instruction>
